cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the specification and verification of communication behavior in distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the programming languages (cs.PL), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper specifically focuses on session types, which are a type-based approach to specifying communication protocols, and this falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses automata theory, which is a topic in the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
